reviews.text: food is unexpectedly delicious and over bistro standards. some dishes are not often found in other French restaurants. Its nearly perfect except the service. Waiters are not very attentive overall and feel like they just want to finish work as soon as possible.  One of them even dropped the wine on sofa (nearly on me) when serving the wine because he wanted to do it quick. of course he didn't notice it as he left immediately.

The best place for lunch, amazing dinner or snack (try quiche Loraine🙏🏼) Great quality of food. Majority of the Hong Kong “wannabe “ restaurants can’t even compare. Really taste like authentic European bistro, reasonably priced, nice service. Roasted veal tenderloin with porcini sauce is out off this world 💙👍🏻

Tasty lunch set at fair price! This is not a busy district so it is usually not crowded even during lunch hour. 

Light lunch can be really "Light", suggest to ask before order if you are not sure how light it is.

Service reasonably fast!
Excellent French restaurant in Hong Kong, the food is fantastic, the ambiance great  and the chef Jerome will welcome you warmly
What an outstanding and authentic French Bistro it is! The steak tartare is almost the best in town and the main courses are absolutely impeccable, especially the Rossini and Duck Magret!
